<h1>NCBBreedbook Privacy Policy</h1>
<p class="updated">Last updated: July 15, 2026</p>

<p>NCBBreedbook is a record-keeping app for dog breeders — dogs, litters, breeding pairs, veterinary records, pedigrees, and finances. This policy explains what information the app handles and how.</p>

<h2>The short version</h2>
<p>NCBBreedbook does not have user accounts, does not use advertising or analytics services, and does not send your data to us or to any third party. Everything you enter — dog records, photos, financial records, pedigrees, and messages from prospective buyers — is stored locally on your device.</p>

<h2>Information the app stores</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Dog and litter records</strong> — names, breeds, AKC registration numbers, microchip numbers, dates of birth, color and health information, and photos you add.</li>
    <li><strong>Veterinary and financial records</strong> — vaccination history, appointment dates, expenses, income, and receipt photos you scan or upload.</li>
    <li><strong>Pedigree information</strong> — ancestry data you enter or scan from paperwork.</li>
    <li><strong>Scanned documents</strong> — photos of registration papers, pedigree charts, or receipts you choose to attach to a record.</li>
    <li><strong>Messages from prospective buyers</strong> — if someone uses the app's "Message the Breeder" feature on a puppy's page, their name and the contact information they choose to provide (email and/or phone number) along with their message is stored so the breeder can follow up.</li>
</ul>
<p>All of the above is stored locally on the device using Apple's on-device data storage frameworks. None of it is transmitted to NCBBreedbook's developer or to any external server, because the app does not currently have one.</p>

<h2>Camera and photo access</h2>
<p>The app requests camera access to let you photograph dogs, puppies, receipts, and paperwork, and photo library access to let you attach existing photos to a record. Images are stored locally as part of the relevant record and are not uploaded anywhere by the app.</p>

<h2>Text messages</h2>
<p>If you choose to hand off a buyer inquiry as a text message, the app opens Apple's own Messages app with the message pre-filled. Sending that message is handled entirely by Apple's Messages app under Apple's own privacy practices — NCBBreedbook does not see, store, or transmit the content of that text itself.</p>

<h2>Data you control</h2>
<p>You can view, edit, or permanently delete any dog record — including its photos, vet history, financial entries, and any related buyer messages — directly within the app at any time.</p>

<h2>Children's privacy</h2>
<p>NCBBreedbook is a business tool for dog breeders and is not directed at children. It does not knowingly collect information from children under 13.</p>

<h2>Future changes</h2>
<p>If a future version of NCBBreedbook adds features that share data outside your device (for example, allowing a buyer to view a puppy's page remotely), this policy will be updated to describe that before the feature becomes available, and the updated date at the top of this page will change accordingly.</p>

